HEADWORD: Shaggy
<hw>Shag"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Shaggier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Shaggiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From <er>Shag</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Rough with long hair or wool.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>About his shoulders hangs the <qex>shaggy</qex> skin.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Rough; rugged; jaggy.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[A rill] that winds unseen beneath the <qex>shaggy</qex> fell.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shag-haired</ent>⟦br⟧
